Learning new software is always interesting, spending countless hours on trying to make something work then finally *pop* you realise that you forgot to put in a semi-colon or didn’t properly name something. After all that time you finally make something, something you wanted to make and it comes out just as you wanted, this is what really makes me happy. Processing is a java based application which allows you to create a whole lot of pretty and colourful pieces. These can be interactive and have the ability to add ‘libraries’ which allow cameras, microphones and even Kinects to be used to make interaction varied and interesting. But first as on all programs I need to learn how to do the basic Hello World..

