For our next lesson in processing we learnt about images and image manipulation. To add an image we name it and put it outside of the draw and setup void areas. With this we can recall the image with the name we give it later on in the draw void. The name I gave to the images was “img” and “img2”, this new class is called PImage.

<code>
void setup(){
img = loadImage("xbox1.jpg");
size(img.width,img.height);
smooth();
} 
</code>

